                                                        <h5 class="faq-accordion__question">
                                                            <div class="faq-accordion__question__content">
                                                                <p>HOW DO WE MONITOR ONLINE EXAMS TO REDUCE THE RISK OF EXAM MALPRACTICE?</p>
                                                            </div>
                                                            <a class="faq-accordion__btn link" href="#" tabindex="-1">
                                                                <span class="faq-accordion__btn__show"><em class="icon-arrow-downward"></em>Show</span>
                                                                <span class="faq-accordion__btn__hide"><em class="icon-arrow-upward"></em>Hide</span>
                                                            </a>
                                                        </h5>
                                                        <div class="faq-accordion__answer faq-accordion__description typography-space-small list-in-article">
                                                            <ol>
                                                                <li>Use of Proctoring software: We use proctoring software to monitor students during online exams. These programs use features such as webcams, microphones, and screen sharing to watch students while they take the exam and prevent cheating. Proctoring software include ProctorU, Honorlock, and Respondus.</li>
                                                                <li>Use of plagiarism detection software: Plagiarism detection software is  used to check for instances of copied text during an online exam. This is to  help detect cheating and other forms of malpractice.</li>
                                                                <li>We set Limit to the amount of time students have to complete the exam: By placing a strict time limit on an online exam, students are prevented from looking up answers or collaborating with others.</li>
                                                                <li>Randomize exam questions:  Randomizing the order of exam questions, it becomes more difficult for students to share answers or collaborate with each other.</li>
                                                                <li>Clear expectations and consequences: Before the exam, we make sure that students are aware of what constitutes malpractice and the consequences of engaging in such behavior. This can help deter students from cheating or engaging in other forms of malpractice.</li>
                                                            </ol>
                                                        </div>
