                                                        <div class="faq-accordion__answer faq-accordion__description typography-space-small list-in-article">
                                                            <p>The Change of Course form is a document used by students to request a change of their academic program at Yonevas Open University. This form is an important tool for students who may have found that their current program of study is not aligned with their career goals or interests.</p>
                                                            <p>The use of this form enables students to apply for a change of course within our institution, without having to go through the admission process all over again. This saves time and resources for both the student and the college.</p>
                                                            <p>To use the Change of Course form at Yonevas Open University, the student would need to fill out the necessary details, such as their current program, the program they wish to change to, and the reasons for the change. They may also need to provide academic transcripts and any other required documentation.</p>
                                                            <p>Once the form is submitted, the college will review the application and determine if the student meets the eligibility requirements for the new program. If the student is approved, they will be notified of the change and provided with a new academic plan.</p>
                                                            <p>Overall, the Change of Course form is an essential document for students who wish to make a change to their academic program at Yonevas Open University. It streamlines the process for students and allows them to pursue their desired academic path without unnecessary delays. </p>

